In [[general relativity]], the '''magnetogravitic tensor''' is one of the three pieces appearing in the [[Bel decomposition]] of the [[Riemann tensor]].

The magnetogravitic [[tensor]] can be interpreted physically as a specifying possible [[spin-spin force]]s on spinning bits of matter, such as spinning [[test particle]]s.

